Software Development – Health Tracker System
First Sprint (Week 6 – 8)

First Sprint Objective
To implement foundational system functionality including user authentication, basic caloric and exercise logging, simple goal management and responsive user interface support.

First Sprint Features

User Authentication and Security

Registration: The system shall allow users to register with:
•	Unique username
•	Valid email address
•	Secure password

Validation and Security
•	Username uniqueness check
•	Email is validated via a regex
•	Password strength value validation via a regex
•	Passwords hashed before DB storage

Login Validation
•	Credential verification against stored values in database
•	Incorrect credentials rejected
•	Session initiated on successful verification

Password Recovery
•	Button to reset password
•	Page to re-enter a new password
•	System must update that user’s password in DB

User Health Profile
•	The system shall capture the following user health attributes:
•	Height 
•	Weight
•	Age 
•	Biological Sex

These attributes shall support:
•	BMI calculation
•	Goal Validatio
•	Caloric Expenditure Modelling

Validation Contraints
•	Height and weight must fall within realistic human ranges
•	Age must fall within acceptable user limits
•	Values mut be numeric

Database Schema and ERDs
A structured relation schema will be developed including 
•	Users 
•	calorieLogs
•	ExerciseLogs
•	Goals

An Entity Relationship Diagram (ERD) will also define 
•	Primary keys
•	Foreign keys
•	Data relationships
•	Entity constraints

Basic Caloric Logging
Users shall manually input 
•	Food names 
•	Caloric value
•	Timestamp

Validation constraints
•	Numeric only
•	Realistic intake bounds enforced
•	Negative values rejected 
A publicly available caloric dataset will be identified for future integration

Exercise logging 
Users log:
•	Activity type out of three subgroups: sport, gym and recreational
•	Active minutes partaking in one of the subgroups
Calories burned calculated initially as = Active minutes x Predefined caloric burn rate

Validation Ensures
•	Numeric values 
•	Realistic daily limits


Basic Goal Setting
Users Shall:
•	Set manual goals
•	Define future target date
•	Goal Logic:
•	Compare user logs to target 
•	Reject if goal has unrealistic value

Basic Responsive UI
•	Minimal dashboard interface
•	Functional forms
•	CSS @media queries for mobile responsiveness
•	Clear validation messaging


First Sprint Test Cases
Authentication Test
•	Duplicate username rejected
•	Invalid email rejected 
•	Weak password rejected 
•	Password stored hashed 
•	Successful login creates session

Caloric Logging Tests
•	Non-Numeric rejected
•	Out-of-Range rejected
•	Valid entry saved correctly

Exercise Tests
•	Invalid minutes rejected 
•	Calculation correct
•	Stored with timestamp

Goal Tests
•	Unrealistic values rejected
•	Goal met logic functions correctly




Second Sprint (Week 9 – 11)

Second Sprint Objective
To extend the system with automated data integration, advanced goal logic, group functionality, leaderboards, email notifications and data visualisation. 

Second Sprint Features
Calorie Dataset Integration
•	Integration of structured calorie dataset
•	Automatic food lookup functionality
•	Macro-nutrient calculation based on food input weight 
•	Ability to add common meals to internal dataset (E.g. Chicken & Rice)
•	Persist saved user meals in a separate table

Exercise Types database expansion
•	Database driven exercise type categories 
•	Subgroups based on predefined structure. For example: 
  o	 Cardio
  o	Strength Training
  o	Bodyweight
  o	HIIT & Circuits
  o	Sports
  o	Mobility & Recovery
•	These will also have their own predefined caloric burn rate, improving accuracy
•	Dynamic retrieval from database

Automatic Food and Macro Calculation
System shall:
•	Retrieve caloric data automatically
•	Adjust macros proportionally to portion weight 
•	Store macro breakdown (protein, carbs, fats)

Historic Data Visualisation
•	Extrapolate historical caloric, exercise, and weight data
•	Generate graphical trend outputs
•	Display development over time
•	Charts to be implemented via backend data processing and frontend visualisation libraries.



Enhanced Goal Logic
•	Complex goal creation (distance/time targets)
•	Automatic goal expiration detection
•	Timestamp goal creation and deadline
•	Prompt user to set new goal if achieved 
•	Prevent invalid goal times 
•	Automatic expired goal notification

Group Functionality
Group creation 
•	Create unique group name 
•	Store group owner

Group membership 
•	Share join link via email 
•	Allow users to join group
•	Allow users to leave group

Group goals and leaderboards
•	Create group-level goals 
•	Track progress of members
•	Generate leaderboard ranking 
•	Notify group via email when goals are met

Email Integration
•	Password recovery emails 
•	Group join link emails
•	Group goal achievement notifications
•	Goal expiry reminders

Security and Data Integrity Enhancements
•	Ensure passwords remain hashed
•	Validate input constraints across all new features





